    <stitle>ALTERNATOR: DELCO-REMY 25-SI SERIES, TYPES 400 AND 450 - REPAIR PROCEDURES</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec id="hl0801405">
        <title>REPAIR PROCEDURES</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="disassemble" graphiccount="1">
            <title>DISASSEMBLY</title>
            <para>After removing the cover plate, cover and gasket, the typical rectifier end frame components are
                exposed to view as shown in
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0801406">Figure 6</hotlnk>. Note carefully the proper connections; then proceed as
                follows:
            </para>
            <figure id="f0801406" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0801406" filename="../figg08/G0801406.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>End View, Cover Removed</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. "R" TERMINAL LEAD</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. FIELD COIL LEAD</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. "R" TERMINAL</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. REGULATOR</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. POTENTIOMETER</callout1>
                    <callout1>6. MOUNTING SCREWS</callout1>
                    <callout1>7. HEAT SINK</callout1>
                    <callout1>8. OUTPUT TERMINAL</callout1>
                    <callout1>9. DIODE (6)</callout1>
                    <callout1>10. REGULATOR LEAD</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">To check the stator and diodes, remove three nuts, three regulator leads, three stator
                    leads, six diode leads and the "R" terminal lead from the three studs.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">To check the field coil, disconnect the two field coil leads from the regulator.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Later on, it may be necessary to separate the drive end frame assembly from the
                    rectifier end frame assembly by removing the shaft nut, washer, pulley, fan, slinger and thru bolts
                    from the drive end.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
